ie8.note_html: In Internet Explorer 8 Object.defineProperty only accepts DOM objects (MSDN reference).

safari5.note_html: In some versions of Safari 5, Object.defineProperty does not work with DOM objects.

ie8.note_html: In Internet Explorer 8 Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor only accepts DOM objects (MSDN reference).

es5shim.note_html: Internet Explorer 6 - 8 do not differentiate between a dense array with undefined values, and a sparse array. Specifically, `0 in [,]` and `0 in [undefined]` both yield false - whereas in a compliant browser, the former would give `false`, the latter `true`. As such, ES5 array iteration methods can only be shimmed reliably when dealing with dense arrays.
